1
00:00:05,257 --> 00:00:07,682
Simple-hearted devotees,

2
00:00:07,682 --> 00:00:10,895
they can race 
to the conclusion,

3
00:00:10,895 --> 00:00:12,784
jump to the conclusion 
instantly.

4
00:00:12,784 --> 00:00:15,657
The leap of faith.

5
00:00:15,657 --> 00:00:18,069
“Kṛṣṇa said that?”

6
00:00:18,453 --> 00:00:20,964
[Leap of Faith—Jump!]

7
00:00:20,964 --> 00:00:25,699
Like those cowherd boys,
the Jamunā Pāni,

8
00:00:25,699 --> 00:00:28,575
“Why, we’re not worried.

9
00:00:28,575 --> 00:00:30,101
This is poison?

10
00:00:30,101 --> 00:00:33,147
The waters …
Jamunā is so sacred,

11
00:00:33,147 --> 00:00:35,348
the waters
have become poison?

12
00:00:35,348 --> 00:00:38,401
Ha-ha!
Anyway, Kṛṣṇa is here,

13
00:00:38,401 --> 00:00:41,046
why should we worry?

14
00:00:41,727 --> 00:00:44,609
What’s there to worry about?”

15
00:00:44,656 --> 00:00:47,515
“Mā śuchaḥ” 
[Bg: 18.66]

16
00:00:47,515 --> 00:00:50,379
Once I was speaking like that
to Guru Mahārāj,

17
00:00:50,379 --> 00:00:54,423
and he went, 
“Deep thinker.”

18
00:00:54,423 --> 00:00:56,286
Because it means,
Kṛṣṇa, “Don’t worry.”

19
00:00:56,286 --> 00:00:58,546
[Laughing]

